cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.COM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The article discusses the fundamentals of small cell wireless networks, their impact on network capacity, and the factors affecting their performance. This aligns with the scope of the cs.NI sub-category. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The article presents a capacity scaling law for ultra-dense small cell networks, which involves the analysis of information transmission and processing. This is relevant to the cs.IT sub-category. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The article mentions the impact of small cell networks on multimedia applications, such as video streaming and gaming. This relates to the cs.MM sub-category. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The article discusses the optimization of small cell network performance, which involves control and management of network resources. This is relevant to the cs.SY sub-category. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - The article briefly touches upon the societal impact of small cell networks, such as their role in bridging the digital divide. However, this is not the main focus of the article, so cs.COM is the least likely sub-category.
